<rules>
	<rule 	Name="AttributeEndsWithAttributeSuffixRule"
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Performance.AttributeEndsWithAttributeSuffixRule, Gendarme.Rules.Naming, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="">
	
		<problem>The type '{0}' is an attribute and by convention the attributes should end with the Attribute suffix.</problem>
		<solution>You should rename the type and append the Attribute suffix.</solution>
	</rule>

	<rule 	Name="EnumNotEndsWithEnumOrFlagsSuffixRule"
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Performance.EnumNotEndsWithEnumOrFlagsSuffixRule, Gendarme.Rules.Naming, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="">
	
		<problem>The type '{0}' is an enumeration and by convention the enums shoudn't end with the suffix Enum or Flags.</problem>
		<solution>You should remove the Enum or Flags suffix.</solution>
	</rule>


	<rule 	Name="UsePluralNameInFlagEnumsRule"
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Performance.UsePluralNameInFlagEnumsRule, Gendarme.Rules.Naming, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="">
	
		<problem>The type '{0}' is a flags enumeration and by convention the flag enums should have a plural name.</problem>
		<solution>You should convert from singular to plural.</solution>
	</rule>


	<rule 	Name="UseSingularNameInEnumsUnlessAreFlagsRule"
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Performance.UseSingularNameInEnumsUnlessAreFlagsRule, Gendarme.Rules.Naming, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="">
	
		<problem>The type '{0}' is an enumeration and by convention the enums should have a singular name.</problem>
		<solution>You should convert to plural to singular.</solution>
	</rule>
</rules>
